description: Palestinian rescue teams have recovered 50 more bodies from the rubble in the Jabalia refugee camp in northern Gaza, bringing the total number of bodies recovered following the withdrawal of Israeli forces from the area to more than 120, according to Press TV.
title: Bodies recovered in Jabalia camp reach 120 as 50 more are found

description: The Organization of Islamic Cooperation (OIC) says in a statement that it “strongly denounced Israel’s illegal measures to undermine the status and role of the UNRWA through attempts to classify it as a ‘terrorist organization’ and strip it of immunities and privileges granted to its employees”.
title: OIC denounces Israel’s moves to classify UNRWA as ‘terrorist’ organization

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s Foreign Ministry on Sunday denounced Nikki Haley for her disgusting demonstration of support for Israel’s massacre in the Gaza Strip.
title: Nikki Haley’s message on artillery shell is support for ‘slaughter of humanity’: Iran

description: TEHRAN - The Iranian Foreign Ministry on Sunday summoned China’s ambassador to Tehran to protest Beijing’s support for the United Arab Emirates’ “baseless claims” about three Iranian islands in the Persian Gulf.
title: Iran summons China envoy, says expects Beijing to rectify position on Persian Gulf islands

description: Lebanese Hezbollah resistance movement has conducted a drone strike against an Israeli military outpost in the occupied Golan Heights in support of Palestinians amid the Tel Aviv regime’s unrelenting ground and aerial offensives in the Gaza Strip.
title: Hezbollah targets Iron Dome battery in Golan Heights

description: Save the Children’s Alexandra Saieh says aid organisations fear the situation in Gaza may worsen.
title: ‘Gaza is witnessing the worst of the worst levels of malnutrition’

description: TEHRAN - The path to winning the Basketball Champions League Asia (BCL Asia) 2024 title has been determined as the groups for the first-ever edition of the event were confirmed in Friday's draw at the Dubai Sports Council in Dubai,  UAE.
title: Shahrdari Gorgan discover fate at 2024 BCL Asia

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s Mehdi Pirjahan won a gold medal in the 4th MoC Grand Prix on Saturday held in Lagos, Nigeria.
title: Iran’s Pirjahan takes gold at Nigerian Grand Prix

description: TEHRAN – Esteghlal goalkeeper Hossein Hosseini has been omitted from Iran's 26-man squad for the FIFA World Cup 2026 and AFC Asian Cup Saudi Arabia 2027 Preliminary Joint Qualification Round 2 Qualifiers – Group E.
title: Hossein Hosseini left out of Iran football squad
